      "writtenOn": "2026-05-13T07:59:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There currently appear to be no tests covering several important cases:\n\n* model extraction\n* an empty model list\n* Gemini error-body parsing\n* a candidate with no content\n* multiple text parts\n* malformed JSON\n* API URL construction\n\nAt minimum, I think we should add unit tests for `extractModels()`, `extractResponseText()`, and `extractErrorMessage()`.\n\nAre Groovy-script tests supported in this project? Gerrit plugins are often Java-based and can use Mockito/JUnit-style testing, so one advantage of implementing this as a Java plugin may be better support for extensive unit tests.",
      "revId": "18832486f419fc1535782fa701f37d280ae86505",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ebabaf66_782df214",
        "filename": "ai/ai-review-agent-gemini-1.0.groovy",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 1006192
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-13T10:47:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The endpoint API is so volatile, and the code is so small, that the time to write and maintain tests will be a lot longer than the stability or probability of errors.\n\nNone of the scripts in this repo have tests, and many other scripts are much bigger and more complex than this one.\n\nIf you have any scripting framework that would be usable and cheap for implementing tests on these lines of code, I\u0027d be happy to evaluate and adopt it.\n\nBear in mind that *tests aren\u0027t tested*, therefore, if the test is bigger and more complex than the code, what\u0027s the probability that the test is broken rather than the code being broken?",
      "parentUuid": "d0a9e9f9_83006391",
      "revId": "18832486f419fc1535782fa701f37d280ae86505",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
